parameters:
Well done for coming, Karin! Would you like some sweets? We
also have Inari sushi!

To be able to eat such sweet confections... I'm glad I've
lived this long.

It's my first time here, but my tongue feels like it's
melting...\I[15]I wonder if I can take some home?

I just can't resist sweets. The desserts at this tea house
are exceptional.

Before this shop was built, this place was just a field... I
wonder when the house was built? It's quite mysterious...

Wow...! The wild strawberries and sugar are intertwined and
it's so delicious\I[15]

I'm glad the children are happy too. The shrine maiden
shopkeeper with her cute animal ears makes it a very nice
shop.
It's like a shrine visit during New Year's, isn't it?
Yugiri-chan? You came to the shop earlier, huh?

Yeah. When I came to check it out, it was already like
this...
Oh, Karin-san and Yugiri-san. You came to the shop, did you?
--Ah! Momiji-san! There are so many customers, aren't there?

Yes. The other day, our master started a sweet shop and it
became popular right from the opening... I'm helping out,
but as you can see, it's quite busy and tough.

Even Oei-san's dumpling shop doesn't have such a line. It
might be the most prosperous in Edo, right?
--Oh! Karin and Yugiri? Good of you to come!
Hello, Masaki-chan. Thanks for helping us out in Atami.

It's nothing, it's nothing! I'm bound by duty. That was a
piece of cake for me. What brings you here?
Well, there's something we would like to ask Masaki-dono--
Excuse me, server! I'd like to place an order~

I'm sorry, but as you can see, the shop is too busy right
now. I can't attend to you at the moment.

Then it's perfect timing. The shop seems to be in a pinch,
so I'll help out too.

Oh! That would be much appreciated! It's been so busy I've
been thinking of hiring some maids.
Momiji-san, please lend me an outfit as well.

...Are you sure about this, Karin-chan? It's quite crowded,
you know?

No worries, no worries! I do customer service at the
dumpling shop too, so serving is a breeze for me--right,
Yugiri-chan?
--What? Am I supposed to help out at the tea house too?
Yugiri is going to help too? That's a relief!
Uh... I will... also... help out.

Thank you very much. Then please, both of you, go ahead and
help.
--Karin and Yugiri began helping out at the Fox Tea House.

Thank you for helping me, Karin-chan. I'll accompany you
when we go to the forest of spirits.

I had to wait forever, but I finally got inside the shop.
With it being this crowded, I wish they would take
reservations.

Even an old man like me loves sweets♪ The treats here are
seriously delicious. Otherwise, there wouldn't be such a
line so soon after opening.

Sugar used to be a luxury item in the past, but now that
it's become accessible even to the common folk, we truly are
living in better times, aren't we?
Please give me this and this♪
